Package math.shell.linearAlgebra.calculator.exceptions

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ErrorMessages
    A list of Strings used for error messages and exceptions
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    IncorrectSyntaxException
    This runtime exceptions is thrown in case where user inputs equation that parser cannot handle
    NoMatrixInQueueException
    This runtime exceptions is thrown in case where user tries to do operation that requires a matrix on last output, but last output not of type OutputType.MATRIX
    NonSquareMatrixException
    This exceptions is thrown in case where user tries to do operation that requires a square matrix on non-square matrix
    NothingInQueueException
    This runtime exceptions is thrown in case where user tries to do operation on last output, but no operations have been performed and nothing in calculator queue
    NotInvertibleException
    This runtime exceptions is thrown in case where user tries to invert a non-invertible matrix
    NotLeadingOneRowException
    This exceptions is thrown in case where user tries to do operation that requires a leading one row, on a non-leading one row
    UndefinedSolutionException
    This exceptions is thrown in case where matrix operation is undefined
    ZeroRowException
    This exceptions is thrown in case where operation requires a non-zero row
